Update of the rapid diagnosis of infectious diseases. I: Bacteria, fungi and parasites. The application of monoclonal antibodies and DNA probes in the clinical microbiology laboratory has resulted in an array of rapid diagnostic tests. The immunofluorescent assay or enzyme-linked immunoassay is widely used in the rapid diagnosis of bacteria eg Group A streptococcus, Legionella pneumophila, Mycoplasma pneumoniae, Bordetella pertussis parasites eg Chlamydia tachomatis, Cryptosporidium species